<div class="tribe-manual">
  <ManualHeader />

  <ManualPageNav @activePage="loom" />

  <div class="container pb-5">

    <div class="alert alert-dark mb-4">
      <div class="row align-items-center">
        <div class="col-md-8">
          <h5 class="mb-1"><i class="fa-solid fa-layer-group me-2"></i>Loom:
            Multi Tribe Hosting</h5>
          <p class="mb-0 small text-muted">One shared infrastructure. Hundreds
            of isolated Threads. Each Thread is a full Tribe + Junction instance
            with its own database, uploads, ports, and static/PHP distribution
            sites.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 text-md-end mt-2 mt-md-0">
          <span class="badge bg-dark me-1">MySQL</span>
          <span class="badge bg-dark me-1">Typesense</span>
          <span class="badge bg-dark me-1">Caddy</span>
          <span class="badge bg-dark me-1">Docker</span>
          <span class="badge bg-dark">Node.js</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="steps-container mb-5">

      <div
        class="step-card open"
        data-step-name="Loom concept architecture threads shared infrastructure"
      >
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge"><i
              class="fa-solid fa-diagram-project"
            ></i></span>
          <span class="step-title">Architecture Overview</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Loom separates
            <strong>shared services</strong>
            (run once) from
            <strong>Threads</strong>
            (one per tenant):</p>
          <div class="row g-3 mb-3">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="card method-item h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h6 class="mb-2"><strong>Shared (Loom)</strong></h6>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-1">Started once with
                    <code>docker compose up -d</code>:</p>
                  <ul class="small mb-0">
                    <li><code>{PROJECT_NAME}_mysql</code>
                      — single MySQL instance, all thread DBs</li>
                    <li><code>{PROJECT_NAME}_tika</code>
                      — shared document extraction</li>
                    <li>Typesense — shared search, namespaced by thread</li>
                    <li>Centrifugo — shared real-time messaging</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="card method-item h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h6 class="mb-2"><strong>Per Thread</strong></h6>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-1">Created by
                    <code>node loom create &lt;name&gt;</code>:</p>
                  <ul class="small mb-0">
                    <li>Dedicated MySQL DB + least-privilege user</li>
                    <li>Four allocated ports — Tribe, Junction, Dist, Dist-PHP</li>
                    <li>Self-contained directory at
                      <code>threads/&lt;name&gt;/</code></li>
                    <li>Own
                      <code>docker-compose.yml</code>,
                      <code>.env</code>, Caddyfiles, uploads, and logs</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="alert alert-light mb-0">
            <strong>Port allocation:</strong>
            Each Thread reserves a block of 10 ports starting from
            <code>THREAD_BASE_PORT</code>
            (default
            <code>13000</code>): +0&nbsp;Tribe, +2&nbsp;Junction,
            +3&nbsp;Dist&nbsp;(static), +4&nbsp;Dist&nbsp;(PHP). Thread 1 →
            <code>13000–13009</code>, Thread 2 →
            <code>13010–13019</code>, and so on.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="step-card"
        data-step-name="Loom prerequisites loom node file root folder setup"
      >
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">1</span>
          <span class="step-title">Prerequisites</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Loom is a single Node.js CLI file called
            <code>loom</code>
            that lives in the project root. No files need to be moved — just
            ensure the prerequisites are in place:</p>
          <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-4">
              <div class="card method-item h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <code>loom</code>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0 mt-1">The CLI file must be in
                    the project root directory</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
              <div class="card method-item h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <code>applications/tribe/</code>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0 mt-1">Tribe application code
                    must be present here</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
              <div class="card method-item h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <code>applications/junction/</code>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0 mt-1">Junction application
                    code must be present here</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="step-card"
        data-step-name="Loom configure env passwords typesense centrifugo"
      >
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">2</span>
          <span class="step-title">Configure Environment</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <div class="command-block">
            <button
              class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
              onclick="copyCmd('cp .env.sample .env', this)"
              type="button"
            >Copy</button>
            <code>cp .env.sample .env</code>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 mb-2">Open
            <code>.env</code>
            and set at minimum:</p>
          <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-3">
              <div class="card method-item">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <code>DB_ROOT_PASSWORD</code>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0 mt-1">MySQL root password for
                    the shared container</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-3">
              <div class="card method-item">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <code>TYPESENSE_API_KEY</code>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0 mt-1">Strong random string —
                    <code>openssl rand -hex 32</code></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-3">
              <div class="card method-item">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <code>BARE_URL</code>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0 mt-1">Base domain for your
                    server (e.g.
                    <code>example.com</code>)</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-3">
              <div class="card method-item">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <code>CONTACT_EMAIL</code>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0 mt-1">Used for SSL certificate
                    registration via Caddy</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 mb-0 small text-muted">Optional:
            <code>PROJECT_NAME</code>
            (default
            <code>tribe</code>),
            <code>THREAD_BASE_PORT</code>
            (default
            <code>13000</code>),
            <code>DEFAULT_TIMEZONE</code>
            (default
            <code>Asia/Kolkata</code>), and Centrifugo keys.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="step-card"
        data-step-name="Loom start shared services docker compose profile loom up"
      >
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">3</span>
          <span class="step-title">Start Shared Services</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Start the shared infrastructure using the
            <code>loom</code>
            Docker Compose profile:</p>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button
              class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
              onclick="copyCmd('docker compose up -d', this)"
              type="button"
            >Copy</button>
            <code>docker compose up -d</code>
          </div>
          <div class="alert alert-info mt-3 mb-0">
            <strong>Note:</strong>
            This starts the shared MySQL, Typesense, Tika, Centrifugo, and any
            other services defined under the
            <code>loom</code>
            profile. The Docker network
            <code>{PROJECT_NAME}_network</code>
            must be running before creating Threads.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="step-card"
        data-step-name="Loom create thread provision new tenant node loom create"
      >
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">4</span>
          <span class="step-title">Create a Thread</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <div class="command-block">
            <button
              class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
              onclick="copyCmd('node loom create acme', this)"
              type="button"
            >Copy</button>
            <code><span class="comment"># Replace "acme" with your tenant name
                (lowercase, 2–31 chars, alphanumeric + hyphens)</span><br />node
              loom create acme</code>
          </div>
          <div class="alert alert-success mt-3 mb-3">
            <h6 class="alert-heading mb-1">What
              <code>create</code>
              does automatically:</h6>
            <p class="mb-0 small">
              Allocates a port block of 10 &bull; Generates
              <code>threads/acme/docker-compose.yml</code>,
              <code>.env</code>, and four Caddyfiles &bull; Creates MySQL DB +
              user, imports schema &bull; Registers in
              <code>threads/.registry.json</code>
              &bull; Runs
              <code>docker compose up -d</code>
            </p>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-1">Verify the allocated ports with:</p>
          <div class="command-block mb-3">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('node portmap', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
            <code><span class="comment"># Shows all container → host port mappings</span><br>node portmap</code>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Thread directory layout</strong>
            (fully self-contained under
            <code>threads/&lt;name&gt;/</code>):</p>
          <div class="command-block">
            <code>
              threads/&lt;name&gt;/<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;docker-compose.yml<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;.env<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;config/tribe/Caddyfile<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;config/junction/Caddyfile<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;config/dist/Caddyfile<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;config/dist-php/Caddyfile<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;applications/tribe/custom/ &nbsp;← per-thread
              customisations<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;uploads/
              &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;←
              user-uploaded files<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;logs/
              &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;←
              container logs
            </code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="step-card"
        data-step-name="Loom CLI commands list start stop destroy logs status recreate upgrade"
      >
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">5</span>
          <span class="step-title">Managing Threads</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="card method-item h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h6 class="mb-3"><strong>Thread Lifecycle</strong></h6>
                  <div class="command-block mb-2">
                    <button
                      class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                      onclick="copyCmd('node loom list', this)"
                      type="button"
                    >Copy</button>
                    <code><span class="comment"># All threads, ports, status</span><br
                      />node loom list</code>
                  </div>
                  <div class="command-block mb-2">
                    <button
                      class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                      onclick="copyCmd('node loom start acme', this)"
                      type="button"
                    >Copy</button>
                    <code>node loom start &lt;name&gt;</code>
                  </div>
                  <div class="command-block mb-2">
                    <button
                      class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                      onclick="copyCmd('node loom stop acme', this)"
                      type="button"
                    >Copy</button>
                    <code>node loom stop &lt;name&gt;</code>
                  </div>
                  <div class="command-block mb-0">
                    <button
                      class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                      onclick="copyCmd('node loom destroy acme', this)"
                      type="button"
                    >Copy</button>
                    <code>node loom destroy &lt;name&gt;</code>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="card method-item h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h6 class="mb-3"><strong>Diagnostics &amp; Maintenance</strong></h6>
                  <div class="command-block mb-2">
                    <button
                      class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                      onclick="copyCmd('node loom logs acme', this)"
                      type="button"
                    >Copy</button>
                    <code><span class="comment"># Tail logs for a thread</span><br
                      />node loom logs &lt;name&gt;</code>
                  </div>
                  <div class="command-block mb-2">
                    <button
                      class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                      onclick="copyCmd('node loom logs acme php_tribe', this)"
                      type="button"
                    >Copy</button>
                    <code><span class="comment"># Specific service</span><br
                      />node loom logs &lt;name&gt; php_tribe</code>
                  </div>
                  <div class="command-block mb-2">
                    <button
                      class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                      onclick="copyCmd('node loom status acme', this)"
                      type="button"
                    >Copy</button>
                    <code>node loom status &lt;name&gt;</code>
                  </div>
                  <div class="command-block mb-2">
                    <button
                      class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                      onclick="copyCmd('node loom recreate-config acme', this)"
                      type="button"
                    >Copy</button>
                    <code><span class="comment"># Regenerate compose +
                        Caddyfiles (keeps .env)</span><br />node loom
                      recreate-config &lt;name&gt;</code>
                  </div>
                  <div class="command-block mb-0">
                    <button
                      class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                      onclick="copyCmd('node loom upgrade-docker acme', this)"
                      type="button"
                    >Copy</button>
                    <code><span class="comment"># Stop, regenerate, pull images,
                        restart</span><br />node loom upgrade-docker
                      &lt;name&gt;</code>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3 mb-0">
            <strong>destroy</strong>
            drops the DB, stops containers, and
            <strong>archives</strong>
            the entire thread directory to
            <code>uploads/threads/{timestamp}-&lt;name&gt;</code>. Thread
            <code>.env</code>
            is
            <strong>never overwritten</strong>
            after initial creation.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="step-card"
        data-step-name="Loom domain SSL certificate set-tribe-domain set-junction-domain Caddy ACME"
      >
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">6</span>
          <span class="step-title">Custom Domains &amp; SSL</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Bind a domain to any Thread service to enable automatic SSL via
            Caddy's built-in ACME / Let's Encrypt integration. The A or CNAME
            record must already point at your server.</p>
          <div class="row g-3 mb-3">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="command-block mb-2">
                <button
                  class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                  onclick="copyCmd('node loom set-tribe-domain acme tribe.example.com', this)"
                  type="button"
                >Copy</button>
                <code>node loom set-tribe-domain &lt;name&gt; &lt;domain&gt;</code>
              </div>
              <div class="command-block mb-0">
                <button
                  class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                  onclick="copyCmd('node loom set-junction-domain acme junction.example.com', this)"
                  type="button"
                >Copy</button>
                <code>node loom set-junction-domain &lt;name&gt; &lt;domain&gt;</code>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="command-block mb-2">
                <button
                  class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                  onclick="copyCmd('node loom set-dist-domain acme static.example.com', this)"
                  type="button"
                >Copy</button>
                <code>node loom set-dist-domain &lt;name&gt; &lt;domain&gt;</code>
              </div>
              <div class="command-block mb-0">
                <button
                  class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
                  onclick="copyCmd('node loom set-dist-php-domain acme app.example.com', this)"
                  type="button"
                >Copy</button>
                <code>node loom set-dist-php-domain &lt;name&gt; &lt;domain&gt;</code>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="alert alert-light mb-0">
            <strong>What happens:</strong>
            The Caddyfile is rewritten with the domain,
            <code>docker-compose.yml</code>
            is regenerated to expose port 443, and the relevant Caddy container
            is restarted. The domain mapping is persisted in
            <code>.registry.json</code>
            and survives
            <code>recreate-config</code>
            and
            <code>upgrade-docker</code>. Ports 80 and 443 must be open in your
            firewall.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="step-card"
        data-step-name="Loom junction password set-junction-password thread security"
      >
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">7</span>
          <span class="step-title">Junction Password</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Update the Junction password for a Thread — the
            <code>.env</code>
            is rewritten and Junction containers are restarted automatically:</p>
          <div class="command-block mb-2">
            <button
              class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
              onclick="copyCmd('node loom set-junction-password acme', this)"
              type="button"
            >Copy</button>
            <code><span class="comment"># Interactive — prompts for password</span><br
              />node loom set-junction-password &lt;name&gt;</code>
          </div>
          <div class="command-block mb-0">
            <button
              class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block"
              onclick="copyCmd('node loom set-junction-password acme myNewPassword', this)"
              type="button"
            >Copy</button>
            <code><span class="comment"># Inline</span><br />node loom
              set-junction-password &lt;name&gt; &lt;password&gt;</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <ManualFooter />

  </div>
</div>

<ManualScripts />
